<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH-SPEED TRAIN TO LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I see that the local politicians are debating whether the proposed Las Vegas 
high-speed train should terminate in Anaheim or Palmdale. 
</P>
<P>
With Southern California suffocating in smog and traffic congestion, billions 
of dollars are proposed to be spent on transporting people on a "gamblers' 
special" train out of the state. I wish I had thought of that! 
</P>
<P>
An even better idea would be to run the train in one direction only -- towards 
Las Vegas. That way we'd solve our congestion problems and I further suggest 
that those politicians debating this non-issue be given free passes on the 
first train. 
</P>
<P>
DON RICHARDSON 
</P>
<P>
Alta Loma 
</P>
</TEXT>
