<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACCOMPANIMENT FOR MEAT, POULTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mix 1 (29-ounce) can undrained peach slices with 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger and 
a few whole cloves in saucepan. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 
about 10 minutes. Serve hot or cold with meat or poultry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102689-0024 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 125673 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 26, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Food; Part H; Page 20; Column 4 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
