<HEADLINE>
<P>
DECISION DUE TODAY ON WHETHER B.H. TO PLAY HAWTHORNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The status of Friday's Bay League football game between Hawthorne and Beverly 
Hills high schools will not be decided until today because of the teachers 
strike in the Beverly Hills Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills Principal Ben Bushman said the Normans will forfeit the game if 
co-coaches Bill Stansbury and Dick Billingsley remain on strike. Beverly Hills, 
scheduled to play host to Hawthorne at 2:45 p.m., forfeited last week's game to 
Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills freshman and sophomore games with Hawthorne have already been 
canceled. ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
