<HEADLINE>
<P>
FALL SPORTS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
OCCIDENTAL NO MATCH FOR CLAREMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last month, the Occidental men's soccer team played one of its best matches of 
the season against conference-rival Claremont, losing in double overtime to the 
Stags, ranked No. 2 in Division III. 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's rematch at Claremont, however, was a different story as Claremont 
raced to a three-goal lead at halftime en route to a 5-0 win in a Southern 
California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference match. 
</P>
<P>
"We couldn't generate any offense at all and we didn't play defense well, 
either," Occidental Coach Lowell Thomas said. "You can't afford to play sloppy 
against a team that good and expect to do very well." 
</P>
<P>
Occidental fell to 6-8-2, 5-4-2 in conference play. 
</P>
<P>
In another soccer match: 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 3, Caltech 2 -- Casey Pirih and Ricky Meyers hooked up on both the 
giving and receiving end to lead Cal Lutheran in a nonconference match at 
Caltech. 
</P>
<P>
Myers scored unassisted at the 14-minute mark to give CLU (11-5-1) a 1-0 lead. 
Pirih scored six minutes later on an assist from Jesse Gallegos for a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Myers scored Cal Lutheran's final goal on an assist from Pirih at the 48-minute 
mark. 
</P>
<P>
College Wrestling 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 22, Bakersfield 21 -- Bakersfield needed a pin in the final match to 
secure a tie, but Moorpark heavyweight David Mitchell managed to hold off 
George Anderson, 20-5, to keep the Raiders unbeaten in Western State Conference 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark (6-1-1, 2-0) won several lopsided matches in building a big lead. In 
the 188-pound class, Moorpark's Delfino Ochoa defeated Steve Ward, 21-6. At 190 
pounds, Moorpark's Carson Wollert beat Steve Sherr, 16-4. Tony Flores of 
Moorpark defeated Jim Frolic, 14-5, at 177 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Robbie Cook (134 pounds), Doug Roberts (142) and Serge Mezheritsky (150) also 
secured wins. 
</P>
<P>
High School Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
Taft d. Kennedy, 15-3, 15-12, 15-8 -- Lynn Pinkus had 14 kills for Taft in a 
West Valley League match at Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Veeck had six kills and three stuff blocks for Taft (3-5 in league play). 
Ali Pickett had eight kills for Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland d. Canoga Park, 15-2, 15-13, 10-15, 15-10 -- Freshman middle blocker 
Michele Diana had a season-high 17 kills to lead Cleveland in a North Valley 
League match at Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland is 9-3, 5-3. 
</P>
<P>
High School Tennis 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 10, La Reina 8 -- Tricia Silverman won three sets at No. 1 singles to 
propel Agoura to a nonleague win at home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
