Sara Lee Corp.: The Chicago-based food company said first-quarter earnings rose 
24% to $93.8 million. The company said improved results were reported despite 
restructuring its food service business, which resulted in an annual loss of 
more than $1 billion in sales. The company said core operations reported solid 
results, with outstanding performance in its personal products businesses. 
Revenue was flat at $2.7 billion. 
