cited lower shipments, higher costs and the effects of unusual items. The 
company said it incurred $15 million in higher costs and lost production 
related to an unexpected outage of its Sparrows Point blast furnace and $8 
million in losses from unauthorized work stoppages at its coal operations in 
July during a labor dispute at an unrelated company. 
