<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
ASSURING BLACK CATS' SAFETY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two black kittens and two black cats now in the Pasadena Humane Society will 
have to wait until after Nov. 1 to find a home because of a moratorium placed 
on the adoption of black cats until after Halloween. 
</P>
<P>
The temporary ban on adoptions of black cats -- in effect this year from Oct. 
16 to Nov. 1 -- began eight years ago out of a desire to protect the animals 
from Halloween party-goers or cult members. 
</P>
<P>
The Humane Society advises owners to keep all pets indoors during the holiday. 
Owners are also advised to refrain from giving animals candy and sweets. 
</P>
<P>
A similar moratorium on the adoption of all animals is also put into effect in 
mid-December to avoid mistreatment of animals bought as Christmas gifts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
