<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: PICO RIVERA; 
</P>
<P>
PRIVATE FIRM WINS CONTRACT TO RUN GOLF COURSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A private company will soon take over maintenance and operation of the Pico 
Rivera Municipal Golf Course. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council has voted unanimously to award the contract to National Golf 
and Tennis Inc. The company will pay the city $1.2 million over a five-year 
period to run the golf course. 
</P>
<P>
The council action is part of a plan to reduce city expenditures by contracting 
with private companies. Next, the city plans to award a private contract to the 
operator of the Pico Rivera Equestrian Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
