<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS: PASADENA, EAGLE ROCK STUDENTS BEST SPELLERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Luz Villarreal 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Pasadena fourth-grader and an Eagle Rock sixth-grader won in their age groups 
in the Plaza Pasadena's spelling bee last week. 
</P>
<P>
Liza Anulao, 11, a sixth-grader at St. Dominic's School in Eagle Rock won the 
fifth- and sixth-grade competition. 
</P>
<P>
Kristina E. VanDusen, 8, a pupil at Longfellow Elementary School, won the 
third- and fourth-grade spelling bee with the word "chocolate." 
</P>
<P>
Two years ago, Kristina won the first- and second-grade competition, and last 
year she won second place in the third- and fourth-grade competition, her 
father said. 
</P>
<P>
More than 200 students from elementary schools in the San Gabriel Valley 
participated in the three-day event. Winners in the first- and second-grade 
competition were announced last week. 
</P>
<P>
Each first-place winner received a trophy, certificate and an encyclopedic 
dictionary set. The spelling bee was sponsored by Encyclopaedia Britannica and 
Plaza Pasadena. Luz Villarreal 
</P>
</TEXT>
