<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: VERMONT AVENUE WORK TO BEGIN WEDNESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A project to renovate a 1 1/2-mile stretch of Vermont Avenue between the 
Griffith Park boundary and Los Feliz Boulevard is scheduled to begin Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The 2 1/2-month project will include reconstruction of the roadway pavement and 
base material, replacement of street lighting, installation of a new curb and 
gutter system, and replacement of broken sidewalks. 
</P>
<P>
The area slated for renovation provides one of the main access routes to 
Griffith Park's Greek Theater, Observatory and golf courses. The roadway has 
been refinished several times, creating a relatively uneven surface. 
</P>
<P>
Traffic will be detoured around Vermont Avenue between 7 a.m. and 3 p.m. during 
the project. Visitors to Griffith Park will be asked to use the park's Fern 
Dell Drive and Commonwealth Canyon entrances. Visitors to the Observatory will 
be asked to use the Western Canyon entrance. 
</P>
<P>
One side of the roadway will be under construction at a time. The west-side 
lane will be the first part to undergo renovation. 
</P>
<P>
Residents of Vermont Avenue will have access to their homes every night but 
will be asked to move their cars or stay away from sidewalks during certain 
phases of the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
