DENTAL HYGIENIST DECISION REVERSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A state appeals court in Sacramento ruled that regulators illegally approved an 
experiment allowing dental hygienists to treat patients without the supervision 
of a dentist, officials said. Under the test program, administered through Cal 
State Northridge, 16 Southern California hygienists were allowed to treat 
patients without a dentist's supervision. All other hygienists are required by 
state law to work with a dentist. The 3rd District Court of Appeal ruled that 
the Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development should have held a 
public hearing on the program before approving the test, which began two years 
ago. 
