<HEADLINE>
<P>
LONGSHOT CASADYS CAPER WINS AT LOS ALAMITOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Casadys Caper, a 7-1 longshot, defeated five older claiming horses in the 
seventh race Wednesday night at Los Alamitos Race Course. Ridden by Ralph 
Pauline, the 4-year-old gelding beat favored Candy Horse and Bigger Better Deal 
to win by a head in 17.79 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Candy Horse broke on top but Casadys Caper and Bigger Better Deal started to 
pull away from the field midway through the race, finishing three-quarters of a 
length in front of third place finisher Winghill Bill. 
</P>
<P>
Casadys Caper paid $16.40, $6.00 and $3.80. Bigger Better Deal paid $4.60 and 
$3.00. Winghill Bill returned $3.60. 
</P>
