<TEXT>
<P>
San Francisco 49er defensive back Jeff Fuller isn't injured as seriously as 
doctors had feared, but it is uncertain whether he will be able to play again. 
</P>
<P>
Fuller was originally diagnosed as having suffered multiple neck fractures and 
damaged nerves in Sunday's game against the New England Patriots, but it has 
since been determined that he chipped three vertebrae in his neck, the team 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Fuller has been moved from the intensive care unit at Stanford University 
Hospital, where he has regained some feeling in his right arm. 
