<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stock Baskets OKd: The Securities and Exchange Commission approved plans by the 
New York Stock Exchange and Chicago Board Options Exchange to begin trading 
"stock baskets." The NYSE product, called the Exchange Stock Portfolio, will 
allow institutional investors, but not individuals, to trade $5-million blocks 
of stocks reflecting Standard &amp; Poor's 500 stock index. The Chicago 
product, also limited to institutional investors, will permit trading in 
$1.6-million baskets based on the S&amp;P 100 index and $1.73-million baskets 
based on the S&amp;P 500 index. The products were recommended in the wake of 
the October, 1987, stock market crash as a means of reducing volatility in the 
markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
