<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON AIRPORT REPORT DUE IN WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city expects to receive a report from the Federal Aviation Administration 
in the next week in response to its request for a investigation into the safety 
of nearby Fullerton Municipal Airport, officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
After the Sept. 16 crash of a light plane in Buena Park, city officials had 
asked the FAA for statistics on the number of crashes at the Fullerton airport 
compared to other facilities the same size. 
</P>
<P>
The city was told by the FAA that preparation of the final report should be 
completed by next week, according to Ken Griffith, the city's administrator of 
planning. 
</P>
<P>
City officials wrote to Jerold Chavkin, regional administrator with the FAA, 10 
days after the latest Fullerton airport accident when a two-seat Cessna 152 
carrying an instructor and a student pilot crashed at the intersection of 
Artesia Boulevard and Darlington Street in Buena Park. 
</P>
</TEXT>
