</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Psychologists were called to Fairfax High School today to help students and 
faculty deal with the death of a 17-year-old youth who fatally shot himself in 
a school restroom in front of two fellow students on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Poindexter, an 11th grader in his first year at Fairfax, was pronounced 
dead several hours after he shot himself about 9 a.m. He apparently had been 
suffering from depression. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses saw Poindexter bring a handgun to school. Some students reportedly 
knew the youth was considering suicide but did not warn teachers, said 
Principal Warren Steinberg. 
</P>
<P>
Steinberg said the two students who witnessed the shooting were not 
acquaintances of Poindexter. Classes were not otherwise interrupted at the 
2,100-student campus west of downtown Los Angeles. 
